Class BiopaxValidator

java.lang.Object
org.biopax.validator.BiopaxValidator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Validator
public class BiopaxValidator extends Object implements Validator
BioPAX Validator Checks All the Rules and BioPAX Elements This is also a registry that keeps validation results: (Validation refers to the BioPAX model and reader, and collects all the errors);

    • report

      public void report(Object obj, String errorCode, String reportedBy, boolean isFixed, Object... args)
      Saves or updates an error/warning case, found by an external tool, in all Validation tasks known to this validator instance. This method is used by, e.g., AOP interceptors, which sense, catch, and register problems that occur in external modules, such as Paxtools, during the data read and/or modify.

      report in interface Validator
